  "about": "Personal narrative, professional philosophy, and career journey of Piergiorgio Roveda",
  "articleBody": "I am a highly adaptable and professional Geographic Information Systems (GIS) Developer with more than 17 years of experience in GEODatabase management, WebGIS development, map analysis processing, geographic data analysis, consulting, video training courses, and operational management in the urban planning and mapping areas.\n\nI consult with clients, create geospatial data, automate data extraction functions, and advise colleagues on performance. I provide administrative, technical, operational, and logistical support to my subordinates to ensure that they have the means necessary to perform a myriad of duties. I am hands-on in my approach and go above and beyond to help those get the most out of the support I provide. My strategy builds trust, establishes rapport, and earns respect from those who have been placed under my leadership.\n\nI consistently receive positive performance feedback and aim for excellence in all my endeavors. I'm ready to contribute my expertise as an asset, ultimately benefiting any organization or team.",
