      "@type": "Article",
      "name": "Desktop GIS Evolution",
      "articleBody": "ArcGIS and MapInfo were the first types of GIS software I started using during my time at university.\n\nQGIS, together with Postgres/PostGIS remains the most suitable tool for each need I have encountered in the last 10 years and I have utilised all the necessary resources to learn it.\n\nI discovered GIS features of MapInfo dedicated to Location Intelligence, in particular Routing, which thanks to the Tom Tom collaboration, has become an excellent tool."
