    {
      "@type": "Article",
      "name": "WebGIS Development Philosophy",
      "articleBody": "The core business of Geomarketing is the production of databases with added value. In fact, customers need to add demographic, social, business and environmental information to their data. The match between internal data and client data input allows to create analyses of market potential, trade value, competition and cannibalization.\n\nAll this data must be entered into dedicated databases and structured in a way that facilitates the analysis. I have cultivated data management in a comprehensive way, starting from collection all the way through to deep analysis.\n\nThe continuous research for software solutions and methods has led me to the development of web interfaces, easy to use and beautiful to consult. These 9 WebApps currently online and accessible only through credentials, are used by about 500 users. The entire Geomarketing team and some of our suppliers use the same WebApps that we deliver to customers, simply because they are faster and more convenient to access than creating a workarea with classic GIS. I have not yet found the same customization possibilities in other WebGIS currently available."
